snippet.textDisplay:
Hopefully Australia learns this time but I highly doubt it.
Too many towns and houses are too close to bushland. There should be a 1km buffer zone around towns and no property should back on to bushland.
Either the towns need to move or the trees cut down around the towns. We can always plant twice, three or five times as many trees 1km away.
Global warming is bad and need to be reversed but let us be honest even without global warming Australia will have bushfires and these sad stories as long as we have towns and property that borders/blends into the forest and is just waiting for a disaster to happen again.
Stay safe all those in line of fire, my prayers are with you
